  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Autumn Day
  author: Lee Saek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    At dawn I climb the high tower, leaning alone at the railing.
    White clouds and green peaks layer upon layer in the distance.
    After rain passes through the courtyard, moss grows ever thicker.
    Across ten thousand miles the sky clears, and the sun rises again.
    My spirit may yet soar proud, but my body has grown old,
    My face withered and drawn, my temples tangled and gray.
    How many times has autumn wind swept through heaven and earth?
    Gazing toward the eastern river, I recall Ji Ying and his distant longings.
  footnotes:
    - Ji Ying (季鷹) was a historical figure known for his nostalgia and longing for his homeland. The reference evokes themes of exile, remembrance, and the melancholy of separation from one's native place.
